projectdescription:
Field Review - Addition / Alteration - Interior alterations to repair fire and water damage to floors 1 to 3 of this existing hotel at this mixed use building on this site.

Revision #1:
1. To move hallway wall to further renovate all Bathrooms and modify their layouts upgrading plumbing fixtures and barrier free walk-in shower stalls in all levels;
2. To upgrade all electrical and lighting fixtures, fire alarm system, internet, wifi and security systems;
3. To install new flooring and replace all guest room entry doors with 36"wide doors;
4. To reconfigure some guest rooms and entry lobby areas, lower and upper lobby;
5. To renovate existing rear basement areas for Laundry, employee lunch room, and office;
6. To demolish existing bar lounge to become a vacant tenant space for future same use;
7. To provide business center for guest use on first level and browsing area in lower lobby for guest uses, and change of use from part of one hotel suite to retail CRU on the 2nd floor;
8. To add: mech, electrical, and structural drawings to the current fire repair and revision scope of work;
9. To provide entrance to the future bar/lounge from the side of the building;
10. To change the permit Architect of record, CRP, and applicant.

OK for Field Review per D.Holbrook

Letters of Assurance:
Schedule A: Johnny Leung (604)729-3632
Schedule B - Arch: Johnny Leung (Jan 2, 2025 - Current)
Schedule B - Elec: Guowei Wang (604)626-2930
Schedule B - Mech & Plum: Alex Lee (604)324-8763
Schedule B - Struc: Li Qing Shi (778)655-9518
Schedule B - Arch: Scott Gordon (604)220-8272  (Jan 25, 2024 - Jan 2 2025)

High Density Housing / Commercial - New Building - To construct a six-storey multiple dwelling building containing 12 units (7 apartment units and 5 townhouse units), over one level of underground parking, having vehicular access from the lane.

*****This permit has been reviewed under the 2014 Vancouver Building By-law (#10908).*****

Permit Amendment #1- January 24th, 2022- S.Le
Refer to DP-2021-00713
•\tAlterations to combine two 5th floor units into a single unit;
•\tThe corridor between Stair 1/elevator and Stair 2 on the 5th floor 
        be removed and replaced with separate entry and exit corridors;
•\tTotal numbers of units decreased by 1 for a total of 11 units;
•\tIn suite storage decreased by one, affecting floor area;
•\tOverall FSR increased from 2.37 to 2.38;
•\tBicycle parking requirements decreased by 1 from 15 to 14;

High Density Housing / Commercial - Addition / Alteration - Interior and exterior alterations to add two floors of residential and office suites to this existing 4 storey mixed use building creating a 6 storey mixed use building. Scope of work includes the removal the existing kitchen exhaust ducts (to be replaced in the future). 

Revision #1 accepted - Mar.6/18
Revision #2 accepted - Jan.2/19
Revision #3 accepted - Dec.20/19 
- raised the 5th and 6th floor level by 2.5';
- replaced ramp with stairs on the 4th floor;
- added additional rises to adjust access to scissor stairs;
- revised access to exit stairs on the basement floor;
- installed new glass railing on the fifth floor roof deck;
- updated elevation and sections to match revised floor plans;
- updated section cc to match previously approved floor plans;
- revised Elevator Shaft to match revised structure drawings;
- relocated structural wall between grid lines B-C and 3-4;
- reconfigure stairs;
- removal of interior wall and storage room in units 101, 200 and 300;
Revision #4 - Accepted July 30/20 - To replace sections of the west exterior wall on the 5th and 6th levels with 1.5 hour rated fire shutters as accepted by AL-2020-00010 and to install glazing on the south end of the central light well on level 6.
Revision #5 - Changes to layout of basement, main and second floors to address challenges with site conditions and to change the electrical engineer from P Leung to D Jamieson effective Feb.19/21. - accepted Apr.20/21
Revision #6 - to demise unit #215 into two separate SRO units and to demise unit #315 into two separate SRO units. - accepted Jan.17/23
